        <section id="keyword-strategy">
          <h2>3. 🔑 Keyword Research &amp; Content Strategy</h2>
          <figure class="image-with-caption">
            <img src="/assets/images/seo/keyword-strategy.webp" alt="Keyword research tools and content planning" />
            <figcaption>Figure 3: Using keyword research tools to plan your SEO content strategy.</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <p>This is where you identify what your audience is searching for and how to create content that meets their needs. In 2025, keyword strategy is about understanding user intent and mapping your content to every stage of the buyer’s journey.</p>
          <p>Many bloggers launching in 2024-2025 are using advanced techniques like semantic keyword mapping and topical authority building. For instance, instead of targeting just “best SEO tools,” they build a network of related articles (“how to use keyword research tools,” “Semrush vs. Ahrefs vs. Moz,” “AI-powered SEO automation”) and interlink them. This cluster approach signals to Google that your site is an authority, helping you outrank even older competitors.</p>
          <p>Use Semrush’s Keyword Magic Tool to discover hidden opportunities, analyze searcher questions, and uncover “zero-click” queries that can win featured snippets. Combine this with competitor gap analysis to find keywords your rivals rank for—but you don’t.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Target Long-Tail Keywords</strong> – These are longer, more specific phrases (e.g., "best budget camera for YouTube beginners"). They have lower competition and higher conversion potential.</li>
            <li>Use <a href="https://www.semrush.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Semrush</a> or <a href="https://ahrefs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ahrefs</a> for finding easy-to-rank keywords by analyzing Keyword Difficulty (KD) and search volume.</li>
            <li>Plan <strong>pillar content &amp; topic clusters</strong> – Create comprehensive, authoritative articles on broad topics (pillars) and link them to more specific supporting articles (clusters).</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Types of High-Performing SEO Blog Posts:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Listicles</strong> – (e.g., "10 Best Laptops for Digital Nomads in 2025")</li>
            <li><strong>How-To Guides</strong> – (e.g., "How to Start a Blog &amp; Make Money")</li>
            <li><strong>Comparison Posts</strong> – (e.g., "SEMrush vs. Ahrefs – Which One is Better?")</li>
            <li><strong>Case Studies</strong> – (e.g., "How I Grew My Blog to $10,000/month in 6 Months")</li>
            <li><strong>Trending Topics &amp; News Articles</strong> (for timely traffic boosts)</li>
          </ul>
