        <section id="onpage-seo">
          <h2>4. 📄 On-Page SEO Optimization</h2>
          <figure class="image-with-caption">
            <img src="/assets/images/seo/onpage-seo.webp" alt="On-page SEO optimization checklist" />
            <figcaption>Figure 4: Checklist for optimizing your blog posts for on-page SEO factors.</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <p>Once you have your content, optimize each page to maximize its ranking potential. On-page SEO is where great blogs pull away from the pack, especially in competitive niches.</p>
          <p>Real-world case studies show that bloggers who consistently use semantic markup (FAQ schema, HowTo schema, Review schema) see higher click-through rates and increased visibility in rich results. Advanced on-page optimization also means using NLP (natural language processing) tools to analyze your content for topical completeness, ensuring you answer every possible user question. Many 2025 bloggers are now using Semrush’s On Page SEO Checker to get actionable suggestions for every article—covering everything from keyword placement to readability and backlink opportunities.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Optimize Title Tags &amp; Meta Descriptions</strong> – Craft compelling, keyword-rich titles (under 60 characters) and descriptions (under 160 characters) to improve click-through rates (CTR).</li>
            <li><strong>Use Header Tags (H1, H2, H3, etc.)</strong> – Structure your content logically. H1 for the main title, H2s for main sections, H3s for sub-sections. This improves readability and SEO.</li>
            <li><strong>Write for Featured Snippets</strong> – Answer common questions concisely within your blog posts using short paragraphs, lists, or tables.</li>
            <li><strong>Internal Linking Strategy</strong> – Link to related posts within your own blog. This helps distribute link equity, improves crawlability, and keeps users engaged.</li>
            <li><strong>Optimize Images</strong> – Compress images for faster loading and use descriptive <strong>alt text for SEO</strong> and accessibility.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="callout pro-tip">
              <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
              <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Implement a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Table_of_contents" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Table of Contents</a> at the beginning of long articles and use bullet points or numbered lists. This significantly improves user experience and can earn you rich snippets.</p>
          </div>
          <p>Don’t forget content pruning: periodically review and update or remove underperforming posts. This keeps your site lean, focused, and authoritative—boosting overall rankings. Always include clear CTAs (calls to action) in every post to convert your SEO traffic into subscribers, leads, or sales.</p>
        </section>
        <hr/>

        <section id="monetization">
          <h2>5. 💸 Monetization – How to Make Money with Your Blog</h2>
          <figure class="image-with-caption">
